The Group Managing Director of NNPC, Kolo Mele Kyari will this afternoon, at the Teslim Balogun Stadium, Surulere, Lagos declare the 18th Nigeria Oil and Gas Industry Games closed. Kyari will be assisted by captains and movers of the Nigerian energy sector, including top management staff of the participating companies. Also, the Minister of State in the Ministry of Petroleum, Timipre Sylva and the Governor of Lagos State, Babajide Sanwo-Olu will be ably represented at the event billed to kick off as early as 10am. Chairman, Local Organising Committee, Aminu Zaria said the games have been very successful as everything has gone as planned and above all, “the athletes have been well behaved and there was no injury during the week-long event.” He disclosed that the closing ceremony will be spiced up by cultural displays that will depict Nigeria’s diversity, adding that, “it will be a spectacle.” In some of the events decided yesterday, five-time table tennis women singles champion, Ogechi Anisionwu was dethroned by Chizoba Onuoha (Shell). In the men’s singles final, Obinna Iloeje of NNPC defeated Bere Barien of Chevron to win the gold medal.    